{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green0\blue128;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 This example shows a one-to-one link. For each person record, one phone number is shown.\par
\par
If no phone number is found, then the word NONE is displayed. This is accomplished by using the \cf2 Success\cf1   property on the link operation.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Sometimes it is convenient to use the "many" part of a link as the main link. For instance, this might be done in a sales report, to list all the items sold but also give information about who bought them.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 If you need to link one record to many sub-records on one screen, you will need to use a subform.\par
\par
When the sub-records are on a subform, they will look and act as though they were part of the same task. However, from a programming point of view, they are in totally separate tasks.\par
\par
This is because each task is designed to handle one Main Source, and only the Main Source can be displayed in tabular format.\par
}
